I like the concept, very interesting. One major complaint I have is the multiple instaliations that the Foundation sent pretty much just to see if they would die. It's a ridiculous waste of valuable researchers and agents. I could see them repeating the experiment once, MAYBE twice with only D-class personnel. Much more interesting would be if the creature had created multiple copies of the original outpost that all did not know about each other. That would give the Foundation cause to be worried about it creating an army.

Also it doesn't HAVE to be underwater. It seems to have few if any identifying characteristics beyond the lights and orifices. You could make the flesh appear more stone like, then have the creature be a (very) small mountain range. Place it in a remote and nearly uninhabited area. Reports eventually reached the Foundation about strange lights on the mountain, during the investigation they established a research base on the mountain, which is the one that was eventually enveloped.







